  <h2>About Broccoli</h2>

  <p class="tagline">
    A cool-season staple that rewards early timing in short seasons.
  </p>

  <p class="lede">
    <strong>Broccoli performs best in cool weather and tolerates light frost.</strong>
    In short growing seasons, the main advantage is that it can be transplanted early. The main risk is heat—warm spells can trigger bolting or loose heads if timing slips.
  </p>

  <p>
    Use the <a href="/tools/seed-start-planner/">Seed Starting Planner</a>
    to calculate frost-based indoor start and transplant windows.
  </p>
